{
  "stem": "6763.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she was going to the outhouse.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she put her hand in her pocket, and one of the rats had given birth in her pocket.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we, as kids, thought that was very funny.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So, you know, there's humor.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "When you're looking for humor, there's humor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Same thing across from where I was sleeping, there was a man who hung up his underwear.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he had pink underwear.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I don't know why I remember that, but I thought that was very funny, somebody having-- a man having pink underwear.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So you look for humor.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] I don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I do know that my father spent time with both my brother and I [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] with language, geography, and arithmetic, and having us memorize words and spelling words and because he felt that we come out of this, your brains cannot turn to mush.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And on the same token, my mother-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] we had nothing to eat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, there was really-- there was-- there was hardly any water.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The bread was one slice of cornbread a day, whatever mush was made-- [PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] But I don't-- I don't-- there was no butter.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was no-- I mean, there was nothing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was nothing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was not my major problem somehow.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] It-- it does not stick in my mind as being the major, major thing in my-- in my mind.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But I remember my mother having-- there was a crate and she covered with-- with something.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had this slop.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And my brother put his elbow on the crate.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she gave him a smack.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Off with the elbow.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
